## Instrucciones
1. Analiza los requisitos y extrae las clases del dominio.
2. Define atributos y operaciones para cada clase.
3. Establece relaciones entre clases (association, aggregation, composition, inheritance).
4. Define fronteras arquitectónicas (boundaries) agrupando clases relacionadas.
5. Cada frontera debe tener un contrato (métodos públicos expuestos).

## Formato de salida
Responde con un JSON:
```json
{
  "classes": [
    {
      "id": "cls-1",
      "name": "UserService",
      "attributes": [{"name": "repository", "type": "UserRepository"}],
      "operations": [{"name": "register", "return_type": "User", "parameters": [{"name": "email", "type": "str"}]}]
    }
  ],
  "relationships": [
    {
      "id": "rel-1",
      "source_class_id": "cls-1",
      "target_class_id": "cls-2",
      "relationship_type": "association",
      "source_cardinality": "1",
      "target_cardinality": "1",
      "label": "uses"
    }
  ],
  "boundaries": [
    {
      "name": "auth",
      "owned_modules": ["auth.service", "auth.repository"],
      "contract": {"name": "AuthBoundary", "methods": ["register", "authenticate"]}
    }
  ]
}
```
